{"key":"processedPost-19001693","value":{"id":19001693,"first":19000255,"last":19002219,"when":1382240705,"utime":"10/20/13 06:45 AM","content":"<blockquote>Quote:<br /><strong>Juiceh said:</strong><br />You can do both in a PC cook food or can food. My AA921 makes a mean stroganoff and I use it to sterilize tools and spawn jars.</blockquote><br />They're great for lobster and crab legs too.&nbsp; For lobster I put 1/2 inch of water in the bottom and bring it to a boil.&nbsp; Drop the lobster in and put on the lid.&nbsp; Bring it up to 5 psi and shut off the stove.&nbsp; Let the pressure drop slowly on its own.&nbsp; Remove, roll in butter and place on the BBQ grill for a few minutes to toast while your steak is cooking.<br />RR<br /><a href=\"https://files.shroomery.org/files/07-009/259775434-Lobster_night_1a.jpg\" class=\"highslide\" onclick=\"return hs.expand(this,{slideshowGroup:'hsg1'})\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"max-width:192px;height:auto;\" src=\"/forums/thumbs/07-009/259775434-thumb_Lobster_night_1a.jpg\"></a>","title":"Re: Pressure canner vs Pressure cooker?"}}